# Project Chimera ‚Äî Agent Rules
# Version: 1.0.0 | Ratified: 2026-03-11 | Authority: Lead Architect

## 1. Spec Enforcement
- NEVER write production code without a ratified spec in `specs/001-chimera-pipeline/`
- Every commit MUST follow: `[SERVICE][SPEC-REF] Description`
- Valid services: `PERCEIVE` | `CREATE` | `ACT` | `LEARN` | `INFRA` | `ALL`
- Valid spec refs: `FR-001`‚Äì`FR-017` | `SC-001`‚Äì`SC-008` | `T001`‚Äì`T064`

## 2. Service Boundaries ‚Äî Single Responsibility
Each service owns EXACTLY one pipeline stage. Never cross boundaries:
- `trend-watcher` ‚Üí owns TrendReport only
- `content-creator` ‚Üí owns ContentBundle only  
- `act-service` ‚Üí owns PostResult + Transaction only
- `learn-service` ‚Üí owns FeedbackReport + TrendSignal only

Services communicate ONLY via HTTP JSON. No shared DB tables. No shared libraries.
All contracts defined in `specs/001-chimera-pipeline/contracts/`

## 3. Forbidden Actions ‚Äî Hard Stops
```
FORBIDDEN-001: Commit secrets, API keys, or tokens to any file
FORBIDDEN-002: Skip ContentSafetyFilter before CREATE ‚Üí ACT handoff
FORBIDDEN-003: Publish content without a valid non-null ContentBundle
FORBIDDEN-004: Auto-approve any transaction above $500 USD
FORBIDDEN-005: Swallow exceptions silently ‚Äî every error MUST be logged
FORBIDDEN-006: Access another service's database directly
FORBIDDEN-007: DELETE or UPDATE any Transaction record (append-only)
FORBIDDEN-008: Use TrendReport older than 24 hours as CREATE input
FORBIDDEN-009: Dispatch FeedbackReport with confidenceScore < 0.6 without human review
FORBIDDEN-010: Push directly to main ‚Äî all changes via pull request
```

## 4. HITL Escalation Thresholds
These thresholds are IMMUTABLE without architect sign-off:

| Trigger | Threshold | Status | SLA |
|---|---|---|---|
| Financial transaction | > $500 USD | PENDING_APPROVAL | 30 min |
| Post publish failures | ‚â• 3 consecutive | HELD_FOR_HUMAN | 2 hours |
| Confidence score | < 0.6 | HELD_PENDING_REVIEW | 4 hours |

## 5. Java Standards
- Java 21+ required ‚Äî `spring.threads.virtual.enabled=true` on ALL services
- All inter-service DTOs MUST be Java Records (immutable ‚Äî no setters)
- `@Version` column required on all shared-state entities (OCC)
- Append-only entities: `Transaction`, `AuditLog`, `PostResult`
- Virtual threads: `ExecutorService.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()`

## 6. Error Logging Mandate
Every caught exception MUST log:
```java
log.error("[{}][{}][{}] {} ‚Äî {}", stage, agentId, operation, errorType, message);
```
Silent catch blocks = FORBIDDEN-005 violation.

## 7. Testing Requirements
- TDD: write test BEFORE implementation
- Minimum 80% coverage ‚Äî enforced by CI, blocks merge
- Testcontainers required for integration tests (PostgreSQL 16 + Redis 7)
- Required test per service: happy path, staleness rejection, HITL trigger, retry behavior

## 8. Dev MCP vs Runtime Skills Separation
- Dev MCP (`.cursor/mcp.json`): tooling for development session ‚Äî Tenx analytics
- Runtime Skills (`.chimera/skills/`): agent capabilities at runtime ‚Äî fetch_trends, generate_content, publish_content, analyze_performance
- NEVER mix dev tooling config with runtime skill definitions

## 9. Security
```
SEC-001: No secrets in source code, Dockerfiles, YAML, or .env files
SEC-002: All secrets via environment variables injected at runtime
SEC-003: ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL must be set or service refuses to start
SEC-004: ContentSafetyFilter runs in BOTH PERCEIVE and CREATE
SEC-005: Trivy scan must pass (zero CRITICAL) before production deploy
```

## 10. Architect Sign-Off Required For
1. Any change to HITL thresholds
2. Any change to Transaction entity schema
3. Any new inter-service dependency
4. Any change to this rules file
